<p>I am using <a href="https://github.com/RobinHerbots/jquery.inputmask" rel="nofollow">Jquery InputMask Plugin</a> in one of my textbox.I have used this plugin in such a way that it accepts only two numeric input.The plugin works fine when textbox intakes two-digit input <code>(Eg: 25)</code> , but when using single-digit input<code>(Eg:09)</code> at the time of retreiving the data the texbox shows the value as <code>90</code> instead of <code>09</code>, although the value which is stored in the database is only a single digit input.</p>  <p><strong>Declaring the plugin</strong></p>  <pre><code> $("#txtPercentage").inputmask("99"); </code></pre>  <p><strong>Extensions used are</strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;script src="~/input-mask/jquery.inputmask.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;script src="~/input-mask/jquery.inputmask.extensions.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; &lt;script src="~/input-mask/jquery.inputmask.date.extensions.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt; </code></pre>